'''变革运动'''（{{Lang-ku|Bizûtinewey Gorran}}），亦称'''变革阵线'''（{{Lang-ku|Lîstî Gorran}}）或'''戈兰'''（意为变革），是[[伊拉克|伊拉克]][[伊拉克库尔德斯坦|库尔德自治区]]的一个政党。目前是库尔德自治区的正式反对党，与[[库尔德斯坦民主党|库尔德斯坦民主党]]和[[库尔德斯坦爱国联盟|库尔德斯坦爱国联盟]]组成的执政联盟对立。该党的领袖是{{Tsl|en|Nawshirwan Mustafa|纳夫施万·穆斯塔法}}。

== 组建 ==
戈兰主要由一些前库民党／库爱盟党员<ref name="CBS">{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2010/05/19/opinion/main6497879.shtml|title=Kurdish Iraq: An Emerging Success|publisher=''[[CBS_News|CBS News]]''|accessdate=2011-02-01|archive-date=2011-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110201112602/http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2010/05/19/opinion/main6497879.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[佩什梅格|佩什梅格]]成员和学者组成<ref name="NYT">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/27/world/middleeast/27kurds.html|title=Gains Seen for Kurdish Challengers|publisher=''[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]''|accessdate=2009-07-27|archive-date=2011-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110501081659/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/27/world/middleeast/27kurds.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他们曾宣称“库民党和库爱盟没有在伊拉克联邦议会上为库尔德人争得什么利益”<ref name="TheEconomist">{{Cite web|url=http://www.economist.com/node/14112538|title=The Kurdish way|accessdate=2011-02-01|publisher=''[[经济学人|经济学人]]''|archive-date=2014-01-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140101004005/http://www.economist.com/node/14112538|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

由于该党的主要目标之一是铲除猖獗的腐败现象<ref name="AlArabiya">{{Cite web|url=http://www.alarabiya.net/articles/2010/10/30/124259.html|title=Goran leaves Iraq's Kurdish alliance with less clout|accessdate=2011-02-01|publisher=''[[阿拉伯卫星电视台|阿拉伯卫星电视台]]''|archive-date=2013-12-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131230232306/http://www.alarabiya.net/articles/2010/10/30/124259.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，因此在库尔德青年之间十分有号召力<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KgEo2q76J_0C&pg=PA146&lpg=PA146&dq=gorran+make+up+iraq&source=bl&ots=MOL6ryN0pP&sig=8ckj3aQ2yvMNjaEwUhx_quHf4SY&hl=en&ei=LQWjTu7NJYSHhQeIw8HYBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CCkQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=gorran%20make%20up%20iraq&f=false|title=Iraq and the United States: creating a strategic partnership - Google Books|date=2009-09-01|publisher=Books.google.co.uk|accessdate=2011-10-20|archive-date=2017-03-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312135200/https://books.google.com/books?id=KgEo2q76J_0C&pg=PA146&lpg=PA146&dq=gorran+make+up+iraq&source=bl&ots=MOL6ryN0pP&sig=8ckj3aQ2yvMNjaEwUhx_quHf4SY&hl=en&ei=LQWjTu7NJYSHhQeIw8HYBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CCkQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=gorran%20make%20up%20iraq&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。支持戈兰的人们希望它“能给库尔德自治区带来更有活力的明天”<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blog.fpc.org.uk/2010/03/up-on-hill-is-where-youll-find-us.html|title=Up on the Hill is where you'll find us|accessdate=2011-10-22|date=March 2010|publisher=blog.fpc.org.uk|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110803200409/http://blog.fpc.org.uk/2010/03/up-on-hill-is-where-youll-find-us.html|archivedate=2011-08-03}}</ref> 、“结束寡头政治”<ref name="Independent">{{Cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/reformist-gains-in-kurdish-vote-shake-iraqs-quiet-north-1762060.html|title=Reformist gains in Kurdish vote shake Iraq's quiet north|publisher=''[[独立报|独立报]]''|accessdate=2009-07-27|archive-date=2009-07-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090730031048/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/reformist-gains-in-kurdish-vote-shake-iraqs-quiet-north-1762060.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

在2009和2010年的选举中，戈兰在[[苏莱曼尼亚|苏莱曼尼亚]]市及[[苏莱曼尼亚省|省]]都取得了胜利<ref name="smh">{{Cite news|url=http://www.smh.com.au/world/change-the-kurds-can-believe-in-20090726-dxit.html|title=Change the Kurds can believe in|publisher=''[[悉尼先驱晨报|悉尼先驱晨报]]''|accessdate=2011-02-01|archive-date=2009-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091011014024/http://www.smh.com.au/world/change-the-kurds-can-believe-in-20090726-dxit.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。英国广播公司在2010年3月的一则报导认为戈兰的出现“已经动摇了库尔德自治区的政局”<ref name="BBC">{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/from_our_own_correspondent/8553321.stm|title=New Kurdish party to challenge polls|publisher=''[[BBC|BBC]]''|date=2010-03-06|accessdate=2017-03-11|archive-date=2017-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824153118/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/from_our_own_correspondent/8553321.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 历史 ==

=== 2009年伊拉克库尔德自治区选举 ===
2009年的选举中，该党的纲领有：地区政府去政治化，加强司法建设，限制政治对经济的干预，让政府的财政预算更加公开透明。该党支持伊拉克实行联邦制，主张利用伊拉克宪法的条文解决地方和中央政府的争执。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://niqash.org/content.php?contentTypeID=75&id=2475&lang=0 |title=Kurdish election lists |date=2009-06-30 |publisher=Niqash.org |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727124015/http://www.niqash.org/content.php?contentTypeID=75&id=2475&lang=0 |archivedate=2011-07-27 |accessdate=2017-03-11 }}</ref>

戈兰的发言人在新闻周刊中说，我们会大力反腐，提高公共服务水平，制定基础设施建设规划。其范围并不仅限于[[苏莱曼尼亚省|苏莱曼尼亚省]]，埃尔比勒省、杜胡克省也在其中。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://europe.newsweek.com/reform-topic-kurdistan-elections-80685?rm=eu|title=REFORM IS TOPIC A IN KURDISTAN ELECTIONS|last=SAMUELS|first=LENNOX|date=2009-06-24|work=新闻周刊|accessdate=2017-03-11|archive-date=2016-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021151402/http://europe.newsweek.com/reform-topic-kurdistan-elections-80685?rm=eu|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在2009年的选举中，戈兰赢得25个席位，成为仅次于库民党和库爱盟的执政同盟（{{Translink|en|Kurdistan List|库尔德阵线}}）的第二大党。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2009/07/25/MNFM18V5US.DTL|title=Iraqi Kurds come out to vote in high numbers|last=Dagher|first=Sam|date=2009-06-26|work=The San Francisco Chronicle|accessdate=2020-10-03|archive-date=2009-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090804034132/http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=%2Fc%2Fa%2F2009%2F07%2F25%2FMNFM18V5US.DTL|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 2010年伊拉克议会选举 ===
2010年选举期间，人们普遍认为戈兰会是库尔德阵线的主要对手，特别是在库尔德爱国同盟控制的地区。这次选举中，戈兰致力于揭露库民党和库爱盟的腐败问题。最后，戈兰赢得8个席位。

=== 2011年库区抗议 ===
2011年，在埃及爆发大规模抗议后，库尔德自治区也爆发了抗议。戈兰在此期间要求内阁辞职，解散库区政府。<ref name="kurdmedia">{{Cite web|url=http://www.kurdmedia.com/article.aspx?id=16609|title=KurdishMedia.com: News about Kurds and Kurdistan|accessdate=2014-05-27|publisher=kurdmedia.com|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419034132/http://kurdmedia.com/article.aspx?id=16609|archivedate=2014-04-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/02/19/us-iraq-protests-idUSTRE71I31Z20110219|title=Iraqis protest in Kurdish region, capital|date=2011-02-19|work=路透社|accessdate=2017-03-11|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924151319/http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/02/19/us-iraq-protests-idUSTRE71I31Z20110219|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="svt">{{Cite web|url=http://svt.se/2.22584/1.2332917/tonarig_demonstrant_dodad_i_irak&queryArt527895=kurdistan&sortOrder527895=0&doneSearch=true&sd=47225&from=siteSearch&pageArt527895=0|title=Tonårig demonstrant dödad i Irak - Nyheter | SVT.se|accessdate=2014-05-27|publisher=svt.se|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121009054731/http://www.svt.se/2.22584/1.2332917/tonarig_demonstrant_dodad_i_irak%26queryArt527895%3Dkurdistan%26sortOrder527895%3D0%26doneSearch%3Dtrue%26sd%3D47225%26from%3DsiteSearch%26pageArt527895%3D0|archivedate=2012-10-09}}</ref><ref>https://www.google.com/hostednews/canadianpress/article/ALeqM5gvqM5KohOmVipuRKfb39gRT968oQ?docId=6029572</ref> 有些人认为戈兰运动不应该增加无意义的混乱，库区政府没必要解散。<ref name="rudaw">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rudaw.net/english/kurds/3452.html |title=Parties Try To Soothe Gorran’s Revolutionary Rage |accessdate=2017-03-11 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110213061403/http://www.rudaw.net/english/kurds/3452.html |archivedate=2011-02-13 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>2011年2月17日，人权观察组织报告称，在 苏莱曼尼亚的库民党总部，由于抗议者向总部投掷石块，守卫至少打死一人，击伤33人以上。<ref name="hrw">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hrw.org/en/news/2011/02/17/iraq-investigate-protester-deaths|title=Iraq: Investigate Protester Deaths | Human Rights Watch|accessdate=2014-05-27|publisher=hrw.org|archive-date=2013-11-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103225747/http://www.hrw.org/en/news/2011/02/17/iraq-investigate-protester-deaths|dead-url=no}}</ref> 枪击一事传出后，[[国际特赦组织|国际特赦组织]]和[[人权观察|人权观察组织]]要求对此事开展独立调查。<ref name="amnesty.org">{{cite web|url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/library/asset/MDE14/006/2011/en/e78f63a5-67e6-4cbd-b25f-58648ff3cd55/mde140062011en.html|title=Document - Iraq: Authorities in Iraq urged to allow peaceful protests | Amnesty International|accessdate=2014-05-27|author=thomas yocum|publisher=amnesty.org|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121007023130/http://www.amnesty.org/en/library/asset/MDE14/006/2011/en/e78f63a5-67e6-4cbd-b25f-58648ff3cd55/mde140062011en.html|archivedate=2012-10-07}}</ref><ref name="amnesty">{{Cite web|url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/library/info/MDE14/005/2011/en|title=Iraq: Restraint urged in the Kurdistan Region of Iraq following protester deaths | Amnesty International|accessdate=2014-05-27|publisher=amnesty.org|archive-date=2012-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006014917/http://www.amnesty.org/en/library/info/MDE14/005/2011/en|dead-url=no}}</ref>
